cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SE, cs.Distributed, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of workflow management systems for Grid computing, which involves distributed computing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper focuses on managing and processing large data sets and executing scientific experiments on distributed resources. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the design and engineering of workflow management systems. 
- cs.Distributed is relevant as the paper focuses on distributed computing and managing workflows on Grids. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as the paper discusses the management of large data sets in the context of workflow management systems for Grid computing.
